metadata.description:
An exploration on the ways in which mental energy might be captured and converted to kinetic destruction.

Each piece begins with an abstract shape. The shape is subjected to a field of disruptors, which contains a combination of beams and bombs. Beams slice through material, shearing fragments generally in the direction the beam is traveling. Bombs shatter material apart and eject shards away from the blast site.

All matter is conserved. That is, if the exploded and scattered fragments were reverted back to their initial positions, there would be a fully intact shape. No virtual particles. üñ§
